# Calendar → QuickBooks Invoicing App — Build Blueprint

**Replaces:** the Google Sheets + Zapier pipelines (MLIG lessons "Monthly Invoices" Zap, MLIE entertainment "MLIE Invoicing" Zap).
**Goal:** one application that reads Google Calendar, turns events into invoices, and pushes them to QuickBooks Online — correctly, idempotently, with no Paths, no 15-column hack, and no duplicate invoices.

---

## 1. Why a rebuild (the original sins we're fixing)

| Problem in the current build | Root cause | How the app fixes it |
|---|---|---|
| Duplicate invoices | Dedup depends on a fragile write-back flipping one cell; mis-mapped column = infinite re-bill | Store the QuickBooks invoice ID per billing group; never create twice |
| YES landing in the wrong column | Sheet layout is column-position-coupled; layout grew, mapping didn't | No positional coupling — data lives in named DB fields |
| Paths + 3 Code-by-Zapier steps | No-code tools can't loop over a variable list of line items | Real code loops over any number of lessons trivially |
| Silent drops ("not found", "no emoji") | No exception surface | Explicit review queue; nothing is billed *or* dropped silently |
| One-row-per-hour throughput | Schedule + single-row lookup | Process a whole billing cycle in one run, on demand or scheduled |
| Two systems (Apps Script + Zapier) handing off through a sheet | Accreted over time | One codebase, one source of truth |

**Core design rule:** store **one event per record** (long format). Group into invoices *at invoice time, in code*. The wide "15 columns in one row" format is what forced every workaround.

