## 2. High-level architecture

```
Google Calendar (lessons cal + gigs cal)
        │  (Calendar API, read)
        ▼
   INGEST  ──► normalize each event → events table (1 row per event)
        │
        ▼
  CLASSIFY  ──► billable | canceled | unconfirmed | unknown-student
        │            │
        │            └─► unknown / ambiguous → REVIEW QUEUE (human resolves, adds alias)
        ▼
   PARSE   ──► student(s), teacher, instrument, duration → price  (rules + optional LLM)
        │
        ▼
 AGGREGATE ──► MLIG: group by student × billing-month → 1 invoice w/ N lines
              MLIE: 1 gig → 1 invoice w/ 1 line
        │
        ▼
  PREVIEW  ──► "what will be billed" screen — verify before any write
        │  (human confirm)
        ▼
   PUSH    ──► QuickBooks Online API: find/create customer, map items, create invoice, (optional) send
        │
        ▼
  RECORD   ──► invoices table (qbo_invoice_id, doc_number, status) + audit_log  ← idempotency lives here
```

The Google Sheet can stay as an optional **read-only mirror** for Lee's comfort, but it is no longer the source of truth or the control valve.

