## 4. Data model

```
funding_orgs        (the "Bill to" — ISS, RAYIM, Hamaspik …)
  id, name, billing_code, qbo_customer_id (nullable until first synced)

students
  id, full_name, funding_org_id (fk), two_digit_code, active

student_aliases     (handles "Ethan" vs "Ethan H.", "Daniella" → Karol, nicknames)
  id, student_id (fk), alias (lowercased, unique)

teachers            (Lee, Jack/JD, Erik …) — used to strip teacher from title
  id, name, aliases[]

price_rules         (duration + instrument → price)
  id, business_line, instrument, duration_minutes, unit_price, qbo_item_name

calendars
  id, business_line ('MLIG'|'MLIE'), google_calendar_id

events              (one row per calendar event — the long-format core)
  id, google_event_id (UNIQUE), calendar_id (fk),
  start_at, end_at, raw_title,
  parsed_student_id (nullable), parsed_teacher, parsed_instrument,
  duration_minutes, unit_price,
  status ('billable'|'canceled'|'unconfirmed'|'unknown'|'billed'),
  billing_period (e.g. '2026-05'), confirmed (bool),
  invoice_id (nullable fk), content_hash

invoices
  id, business_line, funding_org_id (fk), student_id (nullable, for MLIE null),
  billing_period, doc_number (e.g. '03ISS0626'),
  qbo_invoice_id (nullable), status ('draft'|'created'|'sent'|'error'),
  subtotal, created_at, error_message

invoice_lines
  id, invoice_id (fk), event_id (fk), service_date, item_name, description, amount

review_queue
  id, event_id (fk), reason, raw_title, suggested_student_id (nullable),
  resolved (bool), resolved_by, resolved_at

audit_log
  id, ts, actor, action, entity, entity_id, detail (jsonb)
```

**Idempotency keys:**
- `events.google_event_id UNIQUE` → an event is ingested exactly once.
- `invoices (business_line, funding_org_id, student_id, billing_period)` UNIQUE → a student's monthly invoice exists at most once.
- Before any QBO create: if `invoices.qbo_invoice_id` is set, **skip**. This is the single fact that kills duplicate invoices forever.

