## 10. Delivery phases (each phase is shippable)

- **Phase 0 — Foundations (read-only).** Repo, DB schema, Google Calendar OAuth + fetch, QBO OAuth against sandbox, import roster from the existing Master Sheet. *Exit:* events land in the DB; QBO connection proven.
- **Phase 1 — Parse + aggregate + preview (no writes).** Rules parser, classifier, review queue, aggregation, a Preview screen that reproduces the current monthly-billing view. *Exit:* preview matches the current sheet for a known month (this is your correctness oracle).
- **Phase 2 — QBO write with idempotency (behind a confirm button).** Start with **MLIE** (1:1, lowest risk) end-to-end in sandbox, then **MLIG**. Add the double-guard idempotency. *Exit:* invoices appear in QBO sandbox, re-runs create zero duplicates.
- **Phase 3 — Productionize.** Switch to the real QBO company, add scheduler + send-invoice, dashboard polish (run cycle, review queue, audit). **Decommission both Zaps.** *Exit:* a full real cycle billed from the app.
- **Phase 4 — Productize (optional).** Multi-tenant (other music schools / agencies), config-driven business lines, per-client QBO connections. This is the SaaS seed.

